                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>20 Dec 1869</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I have omitted nothing several of your <add>?</add><lb/> but all
                have come duly to hand with the Occidents the last of wh<add>?</add> were<lb/>
                received on the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> You will notice a very
                reasonable <add>?</add> made<lb/> by the Express of only 1/10 per package. I
                    <add>?</add> a statement of <add>?</add><lb/> &amp; disbursements showing a
                small Balance due you. The arrear <add>?</add><lb/> made every effort to collect but
                with little success. <persName>Mr Goodman</persName>
                <add>?</add><lb/> yet insists on not paying. Several I do not ask for prompt
                    <add>?</add>ment<lb/> from—as they would willingly give up their subscriptions.
                I will<add>?</add> remit<lb/> the Balance due you—so soon as I ascertain if any
                thing has been <add>?</add> reud<add>?</add><lb/> to you in
                    <placeName>Phila.</placeName> We have now snow &amp; cold but no Ice—tho we
                    <add>?</add> soon<lb/> to have some. The season has been mild &amp; favorable.
                By the <add>?</add> if<lb/> Railroad we are less distant than ever from
                    <placeName>New York</placeName> this winter the<lb/> trip from <placeName>N
                    York</placeName> to <placeName>Washington</placeName> is now made in 24
                    hours—<add>?</add> in 12<lb/> hours so we are certain 2 to 2 ½ days travel
                    <add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I regret to hear a few differences between yourself &amp;
                    <add>?</add><lb/> congregations—there is yet time for an
                agreement<add>?</add><lb/> satisfactory to all parties. It would be unfortunate if
                    <add>?</add><lb/> work that is considered useful to all should prove
                    <add>?</add><lb/>
                <add>?</add> alone—to harvesting to <persName>Mr Aaron Hart</persName> shall
                    <add>?</add> your<lb/> kind remembrance of her—they are in <placeName>Three
                    Rivers</placeName>. I<add>?</add><lb/> the family entitled to the obituary
                notice in the last Oc<add>cident</add> they<lb/> may be readers but none of them are
                supporters thereof. <add>?</add> have<lb/> little regard for their principles and
                only by the <add>?</add><lb/> are they ever well treated. <persName>Mr
                    Desola</persName> appears well <add>?</add><lb/> here—he is certainly much liked
                and I believe <add>?</add><lb/> few minutes can manage to give benevolent
                    <add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs. Joseph</persName> &amp; child are well.
                    <persName>Miss Rebecca</persName>
                <add>?</add><lb/> a <add>?</add> convenient <sic>traveller</sic> when required to
                    vis<add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs Joseph</persName> desires best regards Believe me</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Truly <add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
